GoDaddy Inc. (GDDY) is Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co. L.P.’s 3rd Largest Position

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 25th, 2017 // No Comments 

Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co. L.P. continued to hold its position in shares of GoDaddy Inc. (NYSE:GDDY) during the first quarter, according to its most recent filing with the SEC. The firm owned 15,517,400 shares of the technology company’s stock at the end of the first quarter. GoDaddy accounts for approximately 10.6% of Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co. L.P.’s portfolio, making the stock its 3rd largest position. Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co. L.P. owned approximately 16.95% of GoDaddy worth $588,109,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
Several other institutional investors have also made changes to their positions in GDDY. Vanguard Group Inc. boosted its position in shares of GoDaddy by 6.8% in the first quarter. Vanguard Group Inc. now owns 5,955,674 shares of the technology company’s stock valued at $225,720,000 after buying an additional 380,343 shares in the last quarter. First Trust Advisors LP boosted its stake in GoDaddy by 4.5% in the first quarter. First Trust Advisors LP now owns 1,575,099 shares of the technology company’s stock valued at $59,696,000 after buying an additional 67,852 shares in the last quarter. State Street Corp boosted its stake in GoDaddy by 6.2% in the first quarter. State Street Corp now owns 591,293 shares of the technology company’s stock valued at $22,412,000 after buying an additional 34,704 shares in the last quarter. MARSHALL WACE ASIA Ltd bought a new stake in GoDaddy during the first quarter valued at approximately $21,303,000. Finally, Marshall Wace North America L.P. bought a new stake in GoDaddy during the first quarter valued at approximately $21,303,000. 




GoDaddy Inc. (NYSE GDDY) opened at 43.60 on Tuesday. GoDaddy Inc. has a 52-week low of $28.13 and a 52-week high of $44.22. The company’s market cap is $3.95 billion. The stock has a 50 day moving average of $42.53 and a 200-day moving average of $38.71. 


 Get GoDaddy Inc. alerts:



GoDaddy (NYSE:GDDY) last released its quarterly earnings data on Tuesday, May 2nd. The technology company reported $0.01 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, beating analysts’ consensus estimates of ($0.04) by $0.05. GoDaddy had a positive return on equity of 0.73% and a negative net margin of 0.28%. The company had revenue of $489.70 million for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $487.77 million. On average, analysts forecast that GoDaddy Inc. will post $0.21 EPS for the current year. 
COPYRIGHT VIOLATION NOTICE: “GoDaddy Inc. (GDDY) is Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co. L.P.’s 3rd Largest Position” was reported by BNB Daily and is owned by of BNB Daily. If you are reading this news story on another domain, it was copied illegally and republished in violation of U.S. & international copyright & trademark law. The original version of this news story can be read at https://www.baseball-news-blog.com/2017/07/25/godaddy-inc-gddy-stake-maintained-by-kohlberg-kravis-roberts-co-l-p-updated.html. 
Several analysts recently commented on the stock. B. Riley restated a “buy” rating and set a $45.00 price target on shares of GoDaddy in a report on Sunday, April 16th. BidaskClub cut shares of GoDaddy from a “strong-buy” rating to a “buy” rating in a report on Tuesday, July 11th. Barclays PLC raised their price target on shares of GoDaddy from $45.00 to $47.00 and gave the stock an “overweight” rating in a report on Wednesday, July 19th. Zacks Investment Research cut shares of GoDaddy from a “hold” rating to a “sell” rating in a report on Thursday, July 6th. Finally, Piper Jaffray Companies reaffirmed an “overweight” rating and set a $50.00 price objective (up previously from $46.00) on shares of GoDaddy in a research report on Tuesday, May 16th. One equities research analyst has rated the stock with a sell rating, four have given a hold rating and ten have issued a buy rating to the stock. GoDaddy presently has a consensus rating of “Buy” and an average price target of $43.75.
In other GoDaddy news, COO Scott Wagner sold 8,000 shares of the company’s stock in a transaction dated Wednesday, May 3rd. The stock was sold at an average price of $39.44, for a total value of $315,520.00. Following the transaction, the chief operating officer now directly owns 10,355 shares in the company, valued at approximately $408,401.20. The sale was disclosed in a filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which is available through this hyperlink. Also, Director Robert R. Parsons sold 8,015,760 shares of the company’s stock in a transaction dated Wednesday, May 10th. The stock was sold at an average price of $37.44, for a total value of $300,110,054.40. The disclosure for this sale can be found here. Over the last quarter, insiders have sold 20,294,413 shares of company stock worth $762,530,369. 25.70% of the stock is currently owned by corporate insiders. 
GoDaddy Company Profile
GoDaddy Inc is a technology provider to small businesses, Web design professionals and individuals. The Company delivers cloud-based products and personalized customer care. It operates a domain marketplace, where its customers can find the digital real estate that matches their idea. It provides Website building, hosting and security tools to help customers construct and protect online presence. 

 
